article.headline: Oregon St. 56, Idaho St. 41
article.story: CORVALLIS, Ore. (AP) -- Seth Tarver scored a career-high 21 points and had eight rebounds as Oregon State defeated Idaho State 56-41 Friday night. Freshman Sean Carter added 10 points on 5-of-6 shooting for the Beavers (2-2). Sophomore guard Austin Kilpatrick scored 14 points and junior center Lucas Steijn had 12 points for the visiting Bengals (1-4). The Beavers shot 33 percent but out-rebounded the Bengals by 15. The game started slowly. But the Bengals led by as many as 14 in the first half and 26-19 at the break. Tarver, a sophomore, put the Beavers ahead for good with a lay-up off an offensive rebound to make it 36-35 with 12 minutes remaining. The game was the opener of the Beaver Invitational, a three-team round-robin. The University of Portland plays Idaho State on Saturday and Oregon State on Sunday.
